main event: A metallic disc-shaped object was observed by a witness in East Orange, New Jersey on July 15, 1963.
interesting points: The object was silver in color and appeared to be a low-flying craft or object.
The object did not make any noise, odor, or leave a trail.
The witness could not attribute the object to any known man-made device.
The witness had previously seen similar objects at various places in New Jersey under different weather conditions.
The witness considered the object to be unidentified and unable to be explained.
